The paper focuses on Monte Carlo search algorithms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) for game playing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses optimization and search algorithms, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The use of multi-armed bandits is a common technique in machine learning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of the discovered algorithms, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
